spirit:register.spirit:name: policy_regs
spirit:register.spirit:description: There is a 32-bit policy register for each memory region. A memory region can be accessible by up to 16 domains. The acces to a memory region controled by two bits for each momory region and domain. The more signifcation bit representing read permisson and the less significant one pressenting write permission. The pairs start from the least significant bits with domain 0.
